  "prompt": "How do I impress people and have a good impression on them?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to make a good impression:\n\n1. Be confident and genuine\n- Maintain good posture\n- Make eye contact\n- Speak clearly and with conviction\n\n2. Practice active listening\n- Show genuine interest in others\n- Ask thoughtful questions\n- Pay attention when someone is speaking\n\n3. Be positive and friendly\n- Smile\n- Use a warm and welcoming tone\n- Show enthusiasm\n\n4. Dress appropriately\n- Dress for the occasion\n- Ensure your clothes are clean and well-fitted\n- Pay attention to grooming\n\n5. Show respect\n- Be polite and considerate\n- Use good manners\n- Treat everyone with kindness\n\n6. Demonstrate competence\n- Be prepared and knowledgeable\n- Share relevant experiences\n- Show your skills and expertise\n\n7. Be authentic\n- Don't try to be someone you're not\n- Be true to yourself\n- Show your unique personality\n\n8. Practice good communication\n- Be articulate\n- Use appropriate body language\n- Tell engaging stories\n\n9. Show empathy\n- Be understanding\n- Demonstrate emotional intelligence\n- Support and validate others\n\n10. Follow up and stay connected\n- Send follow-up messages\n- Maintain professional relationships\n- Keep in touch",
